quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  11,98,He will appear before his folk on Resurrection Day and lead them on to the Fire. How awful will be (their) arrival wherever they are led
  11,99,"They will be followed by a curse in this [world] and on Resurrection Day; how awful is the gift which will be presented [them]"
  11,100,"That is some of the news from towns We are telling you about; some of them are still standing there while [others have been] mown down"
  11,101,"We did no wrong to ´ them but they had (already) wronged themselves; their (false) gods which they had been appealing to instead of to God [Alone] did not benefit them in any way once your Lord´s command came along, and they increased them in nothing except destruction"
  11,102,"Even so will your Lord seize things when He takes over any towns while they are doing wrong; His seizing will be painful, severe"
  11,103,"In that lies a sign for anyone who fears torment in the Hereafter; that will be a day on which mankind will be gathered, and such is a day when (every)one should be present"
  11,104,We will not postpone it except till a deadline which shall be counted out
  11,105,"The day it comes, no soul will speak up except with His permission. Some of them will feel miserable while [others] will be happy"
  11,106,Those who are miserable will be in the Fire; they shall (hear) moaning and groaning in it
  11,107,"remaining there so long as Heaven and Earth will last, except for whatever your Lord may wish. Your Lord is a Doer of whatever He wants"
  11,108,"Those who have found happiness will be in the Garden, living there so long as Heaven and Earth may endure, except for whatever your Lord may wish, as a gift that will never crumble away"